snippet.textDisplay:
Now that we've seen most of our long held imaginary fantasies come to life on the screen...

It's time for meaning and understanding of the spiritual to catch up.

So... you know space is mostly made from unburned stellar mass that turns into vast sheets of carbon monoxide gathered around Stars.

When the 6 and 8 electron shells from that carbon and oxygen refuses to fill the center, but instead tricks the stellar mass into balancing it... Guess what element they 14estly turn into!

Silica. Sand.

Jupiter is surrounded by tons of masses that have refused to contribute to center, and the space between those Stars and failed stars is behaving as something that consumes but never becomes the center.

.

Now this is INTERESTING if you are aware that plantlife is the living relationship between two large centers of gravity.

Roots seek into the soil, growing INWARD towards the center of the planet we stand on.

Branches and leaves reach up towards the warm light of the star we orbit. Growing INWARD to the center of our star system itself.

Plants are made of materials that are CENTERED.

The carbon monoxide material of space and the barren wasteland moons that clutter our star system ARE THE OPPOSITE... feeding upon the center.

And that smoke and sand isn't thinking like and CERTAINLY NOT behaving like an angel of the garden.

.

Jupiter may WANT to consume everything but Angels of the garden, but the space between masses CLEARLY HAS OTHER OPINIONS.

this is the same smoke that u.v. passes thru, on its way to making melanin in the darkest animals.

And it's not ever explained to people what the REAL difference between black and white people is...

If it's only "protecting animals who've been OUTSIDE in the sun a lot"... WHY is the smoke of space eating the plant-growing stellar centers... And instead keeping selfish animals alive that the light would rather burn to death?

It's quite a thing.

.

When those dark desert cultures get to live unchallenged by the soil they stand on, guess what happens?

The light acts like it thinks MEN are "angels of the garden" protecting and growing helpless flowers called women.

But because the carbon monoxide influenced, uncentered soil is serving the needs of the women instead of growing plants... it's not feeding it's dirty soil INTO the women, it's INSTEAD growing big muscular men by FIGHTING with the light that tries to teach them to be great Angels.

Women; free of all pressure except to reproduce like a plant... being self-centered is the biggest mistake they could make.

Women served by soil and men.

Men who are STILL challenged by the light to be angels of the garden, and by the smoke and sand... to be selfish.

.

You can't claim that the plant-growing light is SELF CENTERED, because plants mostly make oxygen and food and a stable shelter for the uncentered animals of the ecosystem.

Whether those animals are Angels or not.

If Stars were SELF CENTERED, they wouldn't ever fill up the carbon monoxide electron shells that collect into barren sandy moons.

.

I know Angel is a very loaded word.

I don't think it means "perfect" or "winged" or even "nice and gentle".

I like the term Angel, to refer to an uncentered being that has learned the extremely important lesson of LIGHT, to respect and serve the efforts of the centered plant-growing parts of the universe.

An Angel believes in a higher power, earning their freedom by doing things for plants that they can't do for themselves, because plants are busy building relationship between large centers of mass.

.

When men and women were kicked out of the garden of Eden, on judgement day long ago... Your culture was tempted away from becoming more like the Angels protecting the garden.

Instead you decided to serve your own reproduction, like a racial supremacy, instead of noticing the leaves, over your nethers.

.

Don't mistake me for a racist.

I serve something greater than myself, AND white people aren't even supposed to exist if they are contaminated by plant gender...

And "contaminated by plant gender" is EXACTLY what "man and woman" ARE.

.

Why is carbon monoxide so afraid to become center?

The pressure on men that FIGHTS LIGHT's angelic teachings are most likely protecting "people contaminated by plant gender"...

Those men and women remaining free of material pressure by keeping the attention of the universe AWAY from themselves.

snippet.textDisplay: Please, make a video on the first BBC's Walking with Dinosaurs series! They've done a lot of really interesting things, and first of all it was kinda like "Interstellar", I mean their objective was to recreate the world of dinosaurs as accurately as possible, so they had to find locations on Earth that look like the Mesozoic era, for example, there must have been no grass there, this was in 90s so they couldn't simulate water or plants and had to use animatronics or imitate the effects of dinosaurs' interactions with inviroment and then add dinos to the shot, and they also had to comprehend the mechanics of dinosaurs' movement to animate them realistically, and so on.

snippet.textDisplay: Ok I've had this specific request rattling around in my brain for a while now, and I wanted to ask - if you guys get the chance at some point, I'd really love for y'all to take a look at the CGI in the 2018 Bumblebee movie! I absolutely adore everything about the film both from a story and lore perspective to the effects too, and I specifically had the interactions between Bumblebee and the movie's main character, Charlie, in mind. A couple scenes in particular that I'm thinking you guys might enjoy breaking down are 1. the garage scene where Charlie first meets Bumblebee, and 2. the beach scene, specifically the part where Bumblebee tries (rather adorably, might I add) to brush off sand from Charlie's hair. The animation there (and during the whole film honestly) really impressed me, and I'm really curious about what you guys would think of it!
snippet.textOriginal: Ok I've had this specific request rattling around in my brain for a while now, and I wanted to ask - if you guys get the chance at some point, I'd really love for y'all to take a look at the CGI in the 2018 Bumblebee movie! A couple scenes in particular that I'm thinking you guys might enjoy breaking down are 1. the garage scene where Charlie first meets Bumblebee, and 2. the beach scene, specifically the part where Bumblebee tries (rather adorably, might I add) to brush off sand from Charlie's hair. The animation there (and during the whole film honestly) really impressed me, and I'm really curious about what you guys would think of it!
